# VPC Peering

VPC peering is a networking connection between two or more VPCs that allows them to communicate with each other as if they were part of the same network.

✅ It enables **private connectivity** between resources in different VPCs.

---

## 📷 Diagram

![VPC Peering](./Images/vpc-peering.png)

---

## 📝 Key Points

- No single point of failure
- Transitive peering not allowed
- You must update route tables
